<item>
            <title>[WICKET-6050] Wicket Ajax (Wicket.From.serializeElement) causes 400 bad request</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-6050</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Due to the recent change (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-5948&quot; title=&quot;wicket-ajax.js probably doesn&amp;#39;t traverse the children of &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; or &amp;lt;span&amp;gt;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-5948&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-5948&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) in Wicket Ajax (JavaScript), Ajax calls add nested form element values as request parameters and result HTTP status code 400 when URL gets too long.&lt;br/&gt;
This happens when you add an Ajax behavior (custom event triggered from JavaScript) to a DOM element with nested form fields.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12921602">WICKET-6050</key>
